Docker commands
docker --version      → Show Docker version
docker info           → System info
docker help           → Help menu
docker images                 → List images
docker pull <image>           → Download image
docker build -t name .        → Build image from Dockerfile
docker rmi <image_id>         → Remove image
docker tag old new            → Rename/tag image
docker history <image>        → Show image layers
docker run <image>            → Run container
docker run -it <image> bash   → Run with shell
docker run -d <image>         → Run in background
docker run -p 8080:80 image   → Map port (host:container)

docker ps                     → Running containers
docker ps -a                  → All containers

docker stop <id>              → Stop container
docker start <id>             → Start container
docker restart <id>           → Restart container
docker rm <id>                → Remove container

docker logs <id>              → View logs
docker exec -it <id> bash     → Enter live container
docker volume create vol      → Create volume
docker volume ls              → List volumes
docker volume inspect vol     → Inspect
docker volume rm vol          → Delete volume

docker run -v vol:/data img   → Use volume in container
docker network ls             → List networks
docker network create net     → Create network
docker network inspect net    → Inspect
docker network rm net         → Remove
docker run --network=net img  → Run container in network
docker cp file.txt cID:/path  → Host → Container
docker cp cID:/path/file .    → Container → Host
docker system prune           → Remove unused containers/images
docker rm $(docker ps -aq)    → Remove all containers
docker rmi $(docker images -q)→ Remove all images
docker system df              → Disk usage
docker compose up -d          → Start all services
docker compose down           → Stop & remove
docker compose ps             → List services
docker compose logs           → Show logs
docker compose build          → Build services
